citeinfo.title: TrainGP
Raines, G. L., Sawatzky, D.L. and Connors, K.A., 1996, Great Basin geoscience data base: U.S. Geological Survey Digital Data Series DDS-41

descript.abstract: Subset from MRDS in 1993 of Carlin deposits. MRDS (USGS Mineral Resources Data System) points and selected attributes for the Great Basin. These data were extracted from the USGS MRDS files in the Fall of 1993. MRDS is a data base of mineralized sites maintained by the USGS.
descript.purpose: The USGS Digital Data Series 41 has broad application and was used by the Reno Field Office for the Great Basin Mineral Assessment (NAMRAP).
descript.supplinf: ARC/INFO point feature types; Single Precision.

overview.eaover: A look-up table gbmrds.lut is used to assign symbols to deposit types. It is used with marker set plotter.mrk. Item Model Name: Blank = not classified; 14A = W skarn; 14AP = pegmatitic W skarn; 15A = W veins; 17 = Porphyry CU; 18A = Porphyry CU, skarn related; 18B = CU skarn; 18C = ZN-PB skarn; 18D = FE skarn; 18DE = FE endoskarn; 18F = AU skarn; 19A = Polymetallic replacement; 19B = Replacement MN; 19C = Distal diseminated AG-AU; 21B = Porphyry MO, low F; 22C = Polymetallic veins; 24A = Cypruss massive sulfide; 24B = Besshi massive sulfide; 24C = Volcanogenic MN; 25A = Hot-spring AU-AG; 25C; Comstock epithermal veins; 25D = Sado epithermal vein; 25EQ = Epithermal quartz-alunite AU; 25F = Volcanogenic U; 25G = Epithermal MN; 25H = Rhyolite-hosted SN; 25I = Volcanic-hosted magnetite; 25KA = perlite; 26A = carbonate-hosted AU-AG; 26C = Sediment-hosted HG; 27A = Hot-spring HG; 27D = Simple SB; 28A = Kuroko massive sulfide; 30C = Sandstone U; 30D = Artillery MN; 31B = Bedded BA; 32C = Kipushi Cu-PB-ZN; 35B.3 = Lacustrine borates; 36A = low-sulfide AU-quartz veins; 37B = Gold on flat faults; 37C = Quartzite-hosted AU; 39A = Placer AU-PGE; XX3 = Iron-Cu-Gold QTZ-DI; XX5 = Zinc veins
